snippet.textDisplay:
Mark: This is Big Papa, Blue Eagle come in.
Ethan: This is Blue Eagle coming in to Big Papa, how's Big Papa doing?
M: Big Papa's good, everything working on your end?
E: This is Blue Eagle, everything's working fine on my end, how about your end?
M: Uhhh equipment check is go, radio check, over.
E: Equipment check coming in to you hot, radio check, over.
M: You got your uhhhhhhhhh radiation detector with you?
E: Radiation detector?
M: You're going to need something down there to detect.
E: That's a negative on the radio detector.
M: All right, mission is a go. Clock starts 1:07 December 12th, 2019.
E: Gimme a kiss goodbye? Over.
M: [exaggerated kissing noises]
E: Kiss received loud and clear, over.
M: Ok. [grunt of lifting] Alright.
E: Oh, that's terrible. M: –No, it's fine– E: Oh my god that's awful.
M: It's fine.
E: Alright.
M: You're going no light?
E: I'm going no light, I think.
M: Alright, wow. Alright.
E: I'm gonna– I'm gonna be a big, brave boy.
M: Ok, cool.
E: This is Blue Eagle heading into the big dungeon, over.
M: Roger that Blue Eagle, do not drop your camera whatever you do, over.
E: Headed down to the deep, dark abyss. Oh boy. Oh, there's really not a lot down here. OK. Oh god. Oh Jesus... Oh lord Jesus.
M: What do you see down there, Blue Eagle?
E: Not a– not a whole lot.
M: Yeah, that sounds about right.
Alright, now I'm gonna– [screeching radio feedback]
E: Come in again, Blue Eagle? [he meant Big Papa]
M: Can you read me? Blue Eagle?
E: Uh, I can read you loud and clear, over.
[more screeching: it sounds like there might be human voices in it, but distorted and high-pitched, like goblins in a high wind]
E: That is the most horrifying noise I've ever heard, over.
M: What's your status, Blue Eagle? What is that noise?
E: I don't know what that noise is, and I really don't like it. Over.
M: Just ignore it for now. Carry on with the mission. I'm going to tell you some facts about this basement that I did not tell you before the mission, for security issues. This basement is not enclosed. I repeat, it is not enclosed. There is access, in every direction, to the exterior of the house. Pretty much at any moment, at any time, anything on the outside could get in.
E: Oh. Well that's super wonderful, thank you so much for telling me… this is a great time. I really hate this.
M: Good to know, Blue Eagle. If you peer your camera down into the small– [static]
E: Into the what, over? Big Papa, Big Papa, come in? This is Blue Eagle, over?
[high pitched static]
E: Oh my God, I fucking hate that.
M: Turn on the light.
E: Agh! Okay, light is on, over.
M: All right, tell me what you see. Is there anything else that might cause interference like that?
E: Let's see. Oh, there is a– there is a work light down here. I don't know if it's– it's not connected to anything, I don't see.
[high screechy static and a beep]
E: Uh–
[almost identical sounds]
E: Mark? Did you turn off the light, over?
M: Ye- wait. Hello?
[static, then unknown voice says "They're here and gettin' mad."]
M: Hello? [static on Mark's end]
E: Uh, Mark, over? Did you turn off the light, over?
M: Hello? Blue Eagle?
E: God, I do not read you loud and clear. The interference is still happening, over.
[static, a screech] M: Can you hear me through the interference?
E: Barely, over. Do you hear it on your end, over?
[brief very high screech]
M: I do not hear it on my end, over. Can you hear me?
E: I can hear you, yeah. Over.
[rumbling plus the high screeching static]
M: Okay. I don't want to alarm you. The motion detectors on the southeast portion of the house have been tripped.
E: Can you elaborate a little more, please? Over.
M: Yeah. There are vibration sensors in the four corners of the house, underneath it. They are both for earthquake detection and for intruders. Just keep an eye out, okay?
E: Okay. Over. Oh– oh– the light, the light is… it was on… oh, I fucking hate this. Oh, I fuckin'–
[high static screech]
E: Uh, hello, over?
M: I read you. I read you.
E: Are you controlling the light, over?
M: No, I'm on the door.
E: The door?
M: Yeah, I have to literally be laying on the ground here for this radio to read you.
E: Are you controlling the light, over.
M: What, what's happening with the light?
E: It keeps coming off and on.
[to us] All right. Mark's going to pass me down the other IR sensor I think, which will make it easier for you guys to see me, cuz I kinda want to– [Mark taps on the door] Yeah! [Ethan taps back] Open!
[high pitched screeching] Ugh. God.
M: What's up? How you doing?
E: I'm doing fine.
M: You good?
E: Yeah, doing great.
M: Ok, cool.
E: Everything is, uh, wonderful. That's all I've got to say—Do you have a head lamp?!
M: If you could try to actually like crawl under those spaces–
E: But this is a new shirt!
M: I got a washing machine.
E: Okay.
M: No, you don't have to.
E: Can I have a hoodie?!
[Amy, from offscreen:] Ethan, say goodbye!
E: Can you hear me?
M: Yeah, Blue Eagle– [Mark hears the screeching for the first time] What is–?!
E: Read you loud and clear!
M: Just be careful down there.
E: All right.
M: If you see anything– there might be nails, creatures, people, um– yeah, just be careful down there.
E: Yup. Alright, well… ok. All right, Mark, I'm going to start crawling into the horrible space, over.
M: I read ya. Is there any sign of that radio demon?
E: No sign thus far. Over.
M: Okay, good to know. Just be careful down there. [brief screech] Something, something's got– [deeper kinda growly static, a couple beeps] Something's got the dogs spooked pretty bad up here.
E: Oh, good. Yeah, that's always a great sign. I'm going to sneak my way in here real quick. Oh god. This is awful. This is so terrible. People could definitely be living back here, and they would never know. Oh my god. [beep] Mark wasn't lying. [beep] There is access to the outside. [beep] I don't know if you guys can see that over there, there is actually [beep] access to the outside. What do we got here? [beep] Something over there. [beep] What is that? [two beeps] I'm not sure… [beeping goes wild] Oh my god. That is the worst noise. There's not much– I, like, can't really crawl [beep] through here much more. There's just not really space. God, I don't see anything. I don't know what's causing the interference. Mark, do you come in? Just doing a general check, over.
E: Do you come in, over? This is Blue Eagle.
[response that sounds like Mark breathing into the walkie-talkie but not saying anything]
E: Mark?
[brief screech]
M: This is Blue– uh, Big Papa to Blue Eagle, giving a general check, how you doing down there?
E: Yeah, I hear you down* there. [*up]
M: I do want to let you know that the proximity sensors have been tripped in all four corners of the house. I don't know what that's about, it's probably just you shuffling around down there, but it's just– I've never had 4 signals at once.
E: Alright. Great. Sounds good, over. Sounds great.
[knocking noise]
E: Oh my god. I heard a knocking noise, is that you, over?
M: I did not hear a knocking noise.
E: OK, great. Yeah, there's knocking.
M: You know, I think you probably checked about all there is to check, um–
[thumping metallic noise]
E: Oh my god. Did you hear that, over?
M: Yes, I did!
E: That wasn't you, over?
M: No, I was right here talking to you.
E: I don't know where the thump came from…
M: I'm going to go check out that noise. You just keep your head on a swivel, okay? Blue– Blue Eagle? Okay? [short screeches]
E: Oh my god, there is so much happening– [more thumps] I don't like it.
M: Blue Eagle, there is something up here.
E: Do you hear that too, over?
[Mark yelling]
E: Oh no! Mark, I'm genuinely scared! I'm genuinely– fuck, I'm genuinely scared! Can I come up? Can I come up, please?? [thumps] Mark?
[muffled noises]
[knocking on basement door]
E: Oh my god, there's a knock. [more knocks] Oh my god, I don't like that at all. I don't like the knocking at all. Ohhh no, I don't like that. Should I–?
[sound of a latch being opened]
E: Oh no, the latch. [thumping] Oh no. [thumping] Oh no!! I don't like this!
[door opens]
[Ethan screaming]

snippet.textDisplay:
Points that show Ethan’s basement maybe actually haunted.

1- at the beginning they had radio inference. Supernatural beings have a knack for inferencing with radio signals that travel through the mortal boundary. The mortal boundary is a field where the living and the dead are cutoff from each other.

2- at 6:11 , Henry and chica started to panic or freak out. Animals can hear and see things we can’t, so in theory chica and Henry saw and sensed something wrong and was trying to warn mark and Ethan. But mostly after Ethan went back down again, trying to search again.

3- at 6:45 , ethans radio started to increase in inference feedback and rapid beeping as he went towards an unfocused object as seen in the clip.

4- 7:48 all four proximity sensors were triggered, Ethan from the prospective of the camera was within the western quadrant of the house.

5- 8:03 - 8:51 , physical interaction was made, contact with Big papa was lost, and knocking proceeded as Ethan made his way to the exit.

One, inference
Two, animal behavior
Three, sensors
Four, lost contact
Five, physical interaction

I’m learning to better understand the paranormal, and this my friend is staged but showed all the clues, steps, and actions taken in this type of situation.

And NEVER go alone.
There are safety in numbers.
